         <abstract><p>Gǝbra Ḥǝmāmāt is the most important Ethiopian service book for the Holy Week.  It is divided into parts for each day and consists of  Biblical readings, commentaries of Biblical passages, 
         homilies, ascetical and dogmatic texts.  The translation was based on Copto-Arabic original but some indigenous material was also added.</p></abstract>
